 # JSX Best Practices

## Conditional Rendering
- Prefer map constants over multiple conditional expressions in JSX
- Define lookup maps at the top level, outside of component functions 
- Follow the pattern: `const COMPONENT_MAP: Record<KeyType, () => ReactElement>` 
- Access components through the map with `{COMPONENT_MAP[key]()}`
- Use TypeScript enums as map keys for type safety when possible

### Example - Poor Practice:
```tsx
// Avoid multiple conditional expressions in JSX
<div>
  {type === 'success' && <SuccessComponent />}
  {type === 'error' && <ErrorComponent />}
  {type === 'warning' && <WarningComponent />}
  {type === 'info' && <InfoComponent />}
</div>
```

### Example - Good Practice:
```tsx
// Define a map constant
const MESSAGE_COMPONENT_MAP: Record<MessageType, () => ReactElement> = {
  [MessageType.SUCCESS]: () => <SuccessComponent />,
  [MessageType.ERROR]: () => <ErrorComponent />,
  [MessageType.WARNING]: () => <WarningComponent />,
  [MessageType.INFO]: () => <InfoComponent />
};

// Use the map in JSX
<div>
  {MESSAGE_COMPONENT_MAP[type]()}
</div>
```

## JSX Simplification
- Extract complex JSX expressions into variables or functions
- Keep render methods clean and focused on structure
- Separate data transformation from rendering logic
- Use early returns for conditional rendering when appropriate
- Break large components into smaller, focused components

## Array Rendering
- Use explicit `key` props with stable, unique identifiers
- Avoid using array index as key when items can be reordered
- Extract item rendering logic to separate components
- Use `map` instead of imperative loops
- Consider performance optimizations for long lists (virtualization)

## Event Handling
- Define event handlers outside JSX using useCallback
- Keep event handlers focused on a single responsibility
- Use descriptive names that indicate both event and action
- Prefer arrow functions for consistent `this` binding

## Props Passing
- Destructure props at the function parameter level
- Use object spread for passing multiple props to a child component
- Be explicit about which props are being passed
- Avoid passing unnecessary props